Overload.descr:
Merges two arrays into one ( ~ symbol can also be used instead).
			Example: 
			let array1 = [0,0];
			let array2 = [1,1];
			let array3 = concatenate(array1,array2); // or let array3 = array1~array2;
			array3 will now return [0,0,1,1].

Can create a custom render target outside of the reserved ones.
			To use, ObjPrim_SetTexturemust have the name of the render target as a string.
			Example:
			CreateRenderTarget("My Render Target");
			ObjPrim_SetTexture(objname,"My Render Target");

Sets the alignment of the text.
			To use center or right aligned text, 
			you have to set the maximum width using ObjText_SetMaxWidth
			(in order to know where the right border is).
			For instance, to align text to the right with a right border at 192 and a maximum width of 300,
			you can use the following:
			ObjText_SetHorizontalAlignment(obj, ALIGNMENT_RIGHT);
			ObjText_SetMaxWidth(obj, 300);
			ObjRender_SetX(obj, 192 - 300);

Returns a random value between the two values.
			Note that the random value is not an integer;
			if you need one, use either round(), ceil(), or floor() on the returned value.
